BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nVufWa951B2lgXnW61yC4
SUMMARY:Improv Happy Hour
DTSTAMP:20260315T225318Z
DTSTART:20260315T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Improv Happy Hour—where comedy is unscripted\, unpr
	edictable\, and unbelievably fun! From movie mashups to literary spoofs an
	d bold\, experimental comedy\, our quick-thinking performers turn your sug
	gestions into hilarious scenes on the spot. This family-friendly show at t
	he iconic Gum Wall in Pike Place Market guarantees a night of laughter\, s
	urprises\, and improv magic you won’t forget. Bring your wildest ideas\, y
	our loudest laughs\, and get ready for a one-of-a-kind comedy experience—b
	ecause at Improv Happy Hour\, anything can happen (and usually does)! Buy 
	Tickets\n\nhttps://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-ho
	ur-2/?occurrence=2026-03-15\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-hour-2/?oc
	currence=2026-03-15
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BLhyNVHOJThVqqilzNSwm
SUMMARY:Show Your Game: An Improvised Game Show
DTSTAMP:20260315T225318Z
DTSTART:20260315T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sundays in March! A Comedy Game Show About Ridiculously Specifi
	c Expertise. Everyone is secretly an expert at something. In Show Your Gam
	e \, professional improvisers and fearless audience volunteers step into t
	he worlds of real-life experts and attempt to survive challenges designed 
	by those experts. Expect strange trivia\, impossible tasks\, wildly specif
	ic knowledge\, and the kind of confidence that only comes from being compl
	etely wrong in public. Maybe it’s acupuncture. Maybe it’s panic packing. M
	aybe it’s Gilmore Girls . Maybe it’s finding creative new places to lose y
	our keys. Inspired by the chaotic brilliance of Taskmaster \, the clever c
	uriosity of QI \, and the unpredictable madness of Game Changer \, every s
	how is completely improvised and completely different. Past topics have in
	cluded haunting\, bubbles\, bedtime routines\, public art\, computer progr
	amming\, low-income housing\, tabletop RPG streaming\, Veggie Tales\, hous
	esitting disasters\, and one unforgettable investigation into a s\n\nhttps
	://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/show-your-game-an-improvised-ga
	me-show-2/?occurrence=2026-03-15\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/show-your-game-an-impro
	vised-game-show-2/?occurrence=2026-03-15
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TWnrTGwBknhRI6GGiv69U
SUMMARY:Matthew Sutton with Bill Radke
DTSTAMP:20260315T225318Z
DTSTART:20260315T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Whether or not you call yourself religious\\\, there’s no denyi
	ng that religion has an impact on society across the continents. And there
	 is no faith more dominant than Christianity in the United States today. W
	ashington State University professor and historian Matthew A. Sutton can s
	how you just exactly how evangelical Christianity entwines itself with all
	 aspects of the country. Drawing from his book\\\, Chosen Land: How Christ
	ianity Made America and Americans Remade Christianity\\\, Sutton chronicle
	s Christians’ five-hundred-year endeavor to turn the U.S. into their versi
	on of the kingdom of God.\n\nhttps://townhallseattle.org/event/matthew-sut
	ton/\n\nFrom Town Hall Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/matthew-sutton/
LOCATION:The Wyncote NW Forum\\\, 1119 8th Ave (Entrance off Seneca St.)\\\
	, Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:town-hall-seattle
CATEGORIES:Town Hall Seattle
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT
END:VEVENT
